      "description": "This 997.2 Carrera S is a definitive example of precision engineering, featuring the 3.8L DFI flat-six engine that provides an immediate, linear throttle response without the vulnerabilities of earlier IMS designs. The 6-speed manual gearbox offers short, tactile throws with perfectly synchronized engagement, paired with a factory mechanical limited-slip differential for superior corner-exit traction. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), maintaining its original damping characteristics and bushing integrity for a zero-deflection driving experience. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, the drivetrain exhibits no oil migration or bore scoring, presenting in a state of mechanical preservation rarely seen outside of a private collection.",
